   "source": [
    "# Classical Methods"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# imports\n",
    "%matplotlib inline  \n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import numpy.random as rng\n",
    "\n",
    "from pylab import rcParams\n",
    "rcParams['figure.figsize'] = 20, 10\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This exercise sheet is split in two parts where the first part is about regression and regularization and the second part is mainly about Linear Discriminant Analysis. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Regression and Regularization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Four different synthetic data sets are provided and your task is to implement different regression models. Please use the function stubs in the following three cells to implement \n",
    "    * Linear Regression\n",
    "    * Polynomial Regression (Optional)\n",
    "    * Ridge Regression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def linear_regression(X, y):\n",
    "    # SOLUTION\n",
    "    return np.linalg.inv(X.dot(X.T)).dot(X).dot(y.T)\n",
    "    # END SOLUTION"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def polynomial_regression(X, y, m):\n",
    "    # SOLUTION\n",
    "    Xs = []\n",
    "    for mc in np.arange(m+1):\n",
    "        Xs.append(X**mc)\n",
    "    Xs = np.vstack(Xs)\n",
    "    return linear_regression(Xs,y)\n",
    "    # END SOLUTION"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def ridge_regression(X, y, m, lam):\n",
    "    # SOLUTION\n",
    "    Xs = []\n",
    "    for mc in np.arange(m+1):\n",
    "        Xs.append(X**mc)\n",
    "    Xs = np.vstack(Xs)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return np.linalg.inv(Xs.dot(Xs.T) + lam*np.eye(len(Xs))).dot(Xs.dot(y.T))   \n",
    "    # END SOLUTION"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Generate data sets"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X1 = np.array(np.linspace(-3,3,100).reshape(1,100))\n",
    "y1 = 3*X1 + 1*rng.randn(100)\n",
    "\n",
    "X2 = np.array(np.linspace(-20,20, 500).reshape(1,500))\n",
    "y2 = (5 * (X2)**2) + 200*np.sin(X2) + 100*rng.randn(500)\n",
    "\n",
    "X3 = np.array(np.linspace(0,np.pi*4,200).reshape(1,200))\n",
    "y3 = 10*np.sin(X3) + 5*rng.randn(200) + 3*X3\n",
    "\n",
    "X4 = np.linspace(0,4,200).reshape(1,200)\n",
    "y4 = -30*X4 + 5*rng.randn(200)\n",
    "\n",
    "num_outlier = 30\n",
    "outlier4 = np.linspace(4,4.2, num_outlier).reshape(1,num_outlier)\n",
    "X4 = np.hstack([X4, outlier4])\n",
    "y4 = np.hstack([y4, outlier4+ rng.randn(num_outlier)])\n",
    "\n",
    "data_sets = [(X1, y1), (X2, y2), (X3, y3), (X4, y4)]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Apply models"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* Please apply all three regression models on all data sets in `data_sets` and visualize the results by\n",
    "   \n",
    "    * plot the data as points\n",
    "    * plot the regressed line.     \n",
    "    \n",
    "* Try different polynomial degrees and different regularization parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

   ],
   "source": [
    "# SOLUTION\n",
    "_, ((ax1, ax2), (ax3, ax4)) = plt.subplots(2, 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "axes =[ax1, ax2, ax3, ax4]\n",
    "                                         \n",
    "for idata_set, data_set in enumerate(data_sets):\n",
    "    X,y = data_set\n",
    "\n",
    "    w_hat = linear_regression(X,y)\n",
    "    y_hat = w_hat.T.dot(X).T\n",
    "    \n",
    "    axes[idata_set].plot(X.T, y.T, \"o\", c=\"b\")\n",
    "    axes[idata_set].plot(X.T, y_hat, c=\"r\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# END SOLUTION "
   ]
  },

    "\n",

    "\n",
    "Z = [[0,0],[0,0]]\n",
